Aggregate planning is the process of developing, analyzing, and maintaing an approximate schedule within a company. In aggregate planning you need to consider costs,inventory, number of employees, desired profit, constraints such as amount of machines or workers available, etc. The goal of aggregate planning is to maximize the use of your resources in the most effective way possible to maximize profit.
Examples of tradeoffs are the cost of holding inventory rahter then just selling it right away, the cost of putting more or less employees on the floor. Everything in business as a trade off, it is important to realize what your options are and how one solution affects anouther.
